hpnicfLBv2.name: hpnicfLBv2

revisions.description: Initial revision of this MIB module.

hpnicfLBv2.description: The private MIB file includes the LB information of the device.

hpnicfLBv2TrapEnable.name: hpnicfLBv2TrapEnable
hpnicfLBv2TrapEnable.description: Indicates whether the module of LB will generate traps for events defined in this MIB. 'enabled' results in SNMP traps; 'disabled', no traps are sent.

hpnicfLBv2ActionEntry.name: hpnicfLBv2ActionEntry
hpnicfLBv2ActionEntry.description: An entry contains the information of the action.

hpnicfLBv2ActionDefaultSF.name: hpnicfLBv2ActionDefaultSF
hpnicfLBv2ActionDefaultSF.description: Default server farm quoted by the action. A zero length string indicates no default server farm has been assigned.

hpnicfLBv2ActionBackupSF.name: hpnicfLBv2ActionBackupSF
hpnicfLBv2ActionBackupSF.description: Backup server farm quoted by the action. A zero length string indicates no backup server farm has been assigned.

hpnicfLBv2ActionInUseSF.name: hpnicfLBv2ActionInUseSF
hpnicfLBv2ActionInUseSF.description: Server farm in use quoted by the action.

hpnicfLBv2ActionRowStatus.name: hpnicfLBv2ActionRowStatus
hpnicfLBv2ActionRowStatus.description: Status of this conceptual row. When create an action, default server farm and backup server farm are optional.

hpnicfLBv2VSEntry.name: hpnicfLBv2VSEntry
hpnicfLBv2VSEntry.description: An entry contains the information of the virtual server.

hpnicfLBv2VSConnectionsLimit.name: hpnicfLBv2VSConnectionsLimit
hpnicfLBv2VSConnectionsLimit.description: Max connections limit of the virtual server. 0 means there is no limit.

hpnicfLBv2VSConnectionsRateLimit.name: hpnicfLBv2VSConnectionsRateLimit
hpnicfLBv2VSConnectionsRateLimit.description: Max connections rate limit of the virtual server. 0 means there is no limit.

hpnicfLBv2VSDefaultSF.name: hpnicfLBv2VSDefaultSF
hpnicfLBv2VSDefaultSF.description: Default server farm quoted by the virtual server. A zero length string indicates no default server farm has been assigned.

hpnicfLBv2VSBackupSF.name: hpnicfLBv2VSBackupSF
hpnicfLBv2VSBackupSF.description: Backup server farm quoted by the virtual server. A zero length string indicates no backup server farm has been assigned.

hpnicfLBv2VSInUseSF.name: hpnicfLBv2VSInUseSF
hpnicfLBv2VSInUseSF.description: Server farm in use quoted by the virtual server.

hpnicfLBv2VSRowStatus.name: hpnicfLBv2VSRowStatus
hpnicfLBv2VSRowStatus.description: Status of this conceptual row. When create an virtual server, default server farm and backup server farm are optional.
